  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Never talk to the police]]></title>
    <link href="http://gnuconsulting.com//blog/2011/02/24/never-talk-to-the-police/"/>
    <updated>2011-02-24T00:41:57-05:00</updated>
    <id>http://gnuconsulting.com//blog/2011/02/24/never-talk-to-the-police</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.kdvr.com/news/kdvr-arvada-police-arrest-11yearold-over-inappropriate-stick-figure-drawing-20110221,0,7099823.story">Ever, ever, ever.</a> Not when you&rsquo;re in the right. Not when you&rsquo;re sure that being cooperative and reasonable will clear things up. Don&rsquo;t let your kid talk to them. Just don&rsquo;t do it.</p>

<p>And yes, that story is obviously police overreacting. But that&rsquo;s the point. Unless your lawyer is present, pretend you&rsquo;re a prisoner of war. Except you&rsquo;re a POW that doesn&rsquo;t even have to give name, rank, and serial number.</p>
]]></content>
